body:
check if you have properly configured your mail server in owncloud, this is done via "hidden" settings (you must manually add them to your config.php file):

```
		$smtpmode = oc_config::getvalue( 'mail_smtpmode', 'sendmail' );
		$smtphost = oc_config::getvalue( 'mail_smtphost', '127.0.0.1' );
		$smtpport = oc_config::getvalue( 'mail_smtpport', 25 );
		$smtpauth = oc_config::getvalue( 'mail_smtpauth', false );
		$smtpauthtype = oc_config::getvalue( 'mail_smtpauthtype', 'login' );
		$smtpusername = oc_config::getvalue( 'mail_smtpname', '' );
		$smtppassword = oc_config::getvalue( 'mail_smtppassword', '' );
		$smtpdebug    = oc_config::getvalue( 'mail_smtpdebug', false );
		$smtptimeout  = oc_config::getvalue( 'mail_smtptimeout', 10 );
		$smtpsecure   = oc_config::getvalue( 'mail_smtpsecure', '' );
```

as you can see the default is local sendmail that should be configured on your php ini with: "sendmail_path"
other modes are "mail" ( use mail() ) and "smtp" (use sockets)
